Most Python users, alas, don't have `pytz` installed, so this will raise an error. And I would prefer a library like this that's so simple to not require time zone importation, when most users don't need that.

Try this instead, it's how I solved the same problem in Skyfield:

    class UTC(tzinfo):
        'UTC'
        zero = timedelta(0)
        def utcoffset(self, dt):
            return self.zero
        def tzname(self, dt):
            return 'UTC'
        def dst(self, dt):
            return self.zero

    utc = UTC()

