@henryiii One last question. I decided to go ahead and type the whole library as a learning experience (as the library is a fairly small and simple library), and I have it all working, but this line I had to ignore. Is there a good way to handle this aside from ignoring it?

Basically, we take either bytes or str and the return will be an Iterator of that same type. ExpandBrace takes a string, so we convert it beforehand and then have to convert return from ExpandBrace back to the type. Mypy doesn't seem to be "smart" enough to see that `is_bytes`'s value was based on our earlier type check, so it gets confused. 

If I do the following, it passes, but that is a waste of time to do. Is ignoring really the best way?

